# Project-Wide Rules

## Database (CRITICAL)

**ALL database changes go through drizzle. No exceptions.**

- NEVER run raw SQL (psql, pg, CREATE/ALTER/DROP TABLE) against the database
- NEVER use `db:push` — it doesn't create migration files and breaks deploys
- Schema changes → edit `web/db/schema/*.ts` → user runs `drizzle-kit generate` → user runs `drizzle-kit migrate`
- Production deploys run `node scripts/migrate.js` which reads `.sql` files from `web/db/migrations/`
- `drizzle-kit generate` is interactive — always ask the user to run it in their terminal

See `.cursor/rules/database-drizzle.mdc` for full details.

## Code Standards

- Files under 500 lines, lines under 150 chars
- Reuse functions, clean up unused ones
- No fallbacks unless explicitly asked
- Respect existing code structure, directories, files, and naming conventions
- Don't add test code unless asked
